    "summary": "Texas has enacted sweeping restrictions on transgender rights: SB 14 bars gender-affirming care for minors and imposes penalties on providers, the attorney general labels such care child abuse, and Medicaid now excludes adult coverage. The state blocks updates to gender markers on identity documents and offers no statewide non-discrimination protections. Hate-crime law omits gender identity, the “panic” defense remains legal, and prisons house trans people case-by-case, usually by birth sex. Schools must not facilitate social transition, bathrooms and sports teams are restricted by sex, and adoption agencies may refuse LGBTQ parents. Together these policies make Texas one of the most hostile states for trans residents despite ongoing community resistance.",
