    "summary": "New York functions as a sanctuary state for transgender people: a 2023 shield law blocks out-of-state subpoenas and custody actions related to gender-affirming care, while no bans or penalties apply to youth or adult treatment.  Residents can self-attest to update birth certificates and driver licences and may choose an “X” marker.  GENDA and related regulations prohibit gender-identity discrimination in employment, housing, public accommodations and insurance, and Medicaid explicitly covers gender-affirming care.  Hate-crime law includes gender identity, the trans-panic defense is barred, and prison housing is handled case-by-case under PREA-based policy.  Schools must allow inclusive restroom and athletics access, though there is no explicit statewide ban on forced outing.  Adoption and foster-care laws protect LGBTQ parents, leaving New York among the strongest states for trans rights despite ongoing safety and data-collection gaps.",
