    "summary": "Florida enacted SB 254 in 2023, banning gender-affirming care for minors, imposing felony penalties on providers, and allowing courts to seize emergency custody of trans youth from affirming parents. Adult patients now face strict in-person and telehealth limits, and the state continues to defend its Medicaid exclusion despite a federal ruling striking it down. The DMV has halted gender-marker updates and birth-certificate changes still require a doctor’s letter, with no “X” option. Florida lacks a statewide gender-identity nondiscrimination law and offers no insurance mandate for transition care. Hate-crime statutes cover gender identity, but the trans-panic defense is still legal. HB 1521 criminalises bathroom use that differs from birth sex in public buildings, schools, and prisons, and SB 1028 bars trans girls and women from female sports teams. Expanded “Parental Rights” rules (HB 1069) effectively force schools to out trans students by requiring parental sign-off for names and pronouns. Prison housing is determined case-by-case, often defaulting to birth sex. With no shield law and policies that treat parental affirmation as potential abuse, Florida is currently one of the most hostile states for trans residents.",
